values:
i've met the most amazing guy who i can't seem to get out of my head. his name is mike, he's a senior at UK, getting ready to go to law school at U of L, and is the sweetest, most gorgeous thing i've laid eyes on. we're kinda inseperable and extremely nauseating to others i'm sure.. but i love it.

sidenote.. i got a b in chemistry, an a in calculus, and a 3.5 gpa for my first semester. i guess you could say i'm freaking OVERJOYED!

i'm home for 2 and a half more weeks.. in which i will immerse myself in all that is christmas, drink lots, play a little taboo, and be with the people i love.

right now.. my life feels so wonderful.
http://imafreakingnut.livejournal.com/10795.html

i feel like i've been seriously out of the loop lately with some people. and you know.. i'm kind of glad. maybe i don't need to know. when i do find things out about these people it's almost always from other sources than that person. i just don't understand how some people could act the way they do. i don't agree with it at all, and i don't understand why you would treat the people that you love and the people that are always there for you the way some people do. maybe i just take things too seriously, or too personally, but really- who's gonna be there for you in the end if you screw everyone over. 

lately i've just felt like forgetting about it. living my life, calling the people i love, seeing those that care about me, and just forgetting about the rest. if someone doesn't even have the decency to treat me with respect on the rare occasions that i do see them, then forget it. i just won't see them.


it feels so good to just get that off of my chest.
http://imafreakingnut.livejournal.com/10608.html

so.. 

my major makes me cry. like hysterically. that's no good.. right?

didn't think so. i'm pretty sure i'd never get through mechanical engineering while managing to have somewhat of a social life and not being stressed out 24/7. 

i'm pretty sure i'm dropping my m.e. 101 class (which will put me at 14 hours.. that's enough right?) and being undecided for the first, and possibly second semester. then maybe accounting? psychology? ANYTHING BUT ENGINEERING!!?! yep.. sounds like a much better plan.

i don't want to spend my entire freshman year crying and stressing out.. and if that means taking less classes and dropping majors and feeling like a bit of a failure.. who cares. 

alex.. you are so right about south campus. during floor meetings i find myself gawking at the blonde sorority girls wondering "do you have a brain?" they seriously drive me nuts. 

so if you couldn't tell college has been a bit of a drag so far. it'll get better though.

yesterday i got a phone call from tommy, one of the guys we hung out with on spring break, saying that chad, another guy we were with, had died the night before. i know we weren't that close to these guys, but we had spent the previous week living, eating, showering, and sleeping with them (in a non-sexual way that is). 
this guy chad was seriously the most awesome kid ever. he was such a sweet heart and had the best manners. the first day i met him i think he opened like 10 doors for me, and when there wasn't enough room for us at the table him and his friends got up and stood in the hallway to eat dinner. chad had the most contagious laugh i've ever heard. it was really loud and goofy. he said definitely in like every other sentence. i'm pretty sure it was his favorite word. 
he died when they got back to south carolina. he drives a mustang and was going 120 when his back end locked up. the cop said he was probably going around 80 when they hit the curb. his car flipped twice, threw him out of the window, then flipped again... landing on top of him. 
i just can't fathom it. i really don't understand why things like this have to happen. i hate that i'll never get to see him again. we had already started planning a road trip down to south carolina when we found out.. and now it just won't be the same. 
i guess in these situations all you can do is pray that he's in a better place.

1. List ten things you want to say to people but know you never will.
2. Don't say who they are.
3. Never discuss it again.

one. i think the way you've acted in the past is completely disgusting and hypocritical.
two. i honestly have never trusted you, but it still enrages me that you would tell people such complete lies about me.
three. you had me.. more than you'll ever know.
four. you drive me up the wall when you say "no.. that boy isn't very cute at all" to be quite frank those guys were so far out of your league it was ridiculous. get over yourself.
five. wash your hair.
six. everyone knows that when you lift up your shirt and say "i'm so fat" you're completely sucking your gut in (even though you don't need to because you really are thin) and you just do that kind of thing so that someone will tell you how thin you really are. it's pretty pathetic.
seven. stop talking about your boyfriend and all of the sex you all have, stop thinking that everyone wants his nuts, and tone down the PDA. it's seriously nauseating.
eight. you have all of the annoying mannerisms of a lame freshman.
nine. i hate that you have a girlfriend. i don't want to date you... but i liked knowing that i could have you.
ten. you're fat and you're rude, you aren't that smart... you pretty much have nothing going for you. try being nicer.






spring break was tons of fun.. pictures to come very soon.

so i'm supposed to give an 8-10 minute persuasive speech tomorrow.. don't really know what i'll be persuading my audience to do, but hey.. it'll come to me. 

my views on the infamous "senior slide"...      it's not that we are too lazy to do the work or don't have enough time.. it's that the work is completely pointless and i will gain absolutely nothing from doing it, other than a good GPA and some keys money. but really.. it just doesn't matter much anymore.

so.. i believe from here on out i will do just enough work to have b's in my classes and study enough to learn the concepts of AP Calculus.. since that's basically the only subject i'm really going to need next year. 

25 more days until spring break? freaking wonderful. 

good lord senior year will be done in 2 months and 21 days and it could not come ANY sooner!!

anyways.. i've been pretty lucky lately. just with little things, but hey.. luck is luck.

but anyways.. it was a good time. i cannot wait for college. i have a feeling UK is going to be great times. AAAAND.. engineering is looking like an alright major.

this weekend i'm off to uk to visit my cousin and go to some of her engineering classes. i also have a meeting with one of the engineering advisors. i'm not quite sure this is what i want to do.. but i figure it'll work for now. i love calculus, but if i end up hating engineering i can always switch.

next weekend: sushi for my birthday and connections with laura. this girl is so excited about becoming an adult! haha

okay.. so this summer i'm going to europe with my school and apparently their plugs are different over there..?? and even though it is in the not so near future i'm still starting to think about it already. so, i was wondering if anyone i knew had a converter thing so i wouldn't have to spend the money to buy one, which i'll only use for these two weeks. i don't even know what they really are but apparently they exist. well, if you understand what i mean and can be of any assistance pleeeeeeease let me know and i shall repay you with scrumptious baked goods and such. 

in other news.. 

today was good. had a really good workout with katie, not much homework at all, tomorrow is friday! ah i love weekends. i live for weekends. but really, who doesn't?

so yesterday i get my schedule for spalding for the fourth session. i'm taking effective speaking. i signed up for ethics. lovely. apparently the registration office made a mistake and by the time i found out the class was full. and to make the situation even better, my old philosophy professor who is absolutely wonderful is teaching the class. :( oh well.. this class should be majorly easy so i guess i can't really complain. 

tonight = vegetarian night. eggplant pizzas and salad. mmmmm. i think i might try to be a vegetarian. the only think i would REALLY miss would be chicken, but hey.. i'd live.

yesterday my true love waits ring fell off. i don't know when and i don't know where. my guess is that i accidently pulled it off while drying my hands at some point, because i tend to do that. when i first noticed i had the weirdest feeling of like.. anxiety. i can't really think of how else to describe it, but it was the worst feeling in the world. that ring is like my comfort blanket almost. i hope i find it. i kinda doubt i will though..

tiempo para cena.. mmmmmmm. (check out those mad espanol skills)
http://imafreakingnut.livejournal.com/4088.html

last night my sister, katie, and i went out for sushi at sapporo, which was absolutely delicious! if you like sushi and have yet to eat at this restaurant you MUST go there at your earliest convenience :) and get a crunch munch roll or tempura roll. mmmmmm lovely

after that katie and i were going to go to a party out in fisherville, but didn't.. because it was in fisherville. last time we tried going to a party out there we got miserably lost.. drove around until we found the expressway, came back to civilization, and ended up going to this girl's party that lived literally 5 minutes away from me. that was a funny night though. 

so.. instead we came back here, ate some apple pie with my parents and grandparents, then went to village 8 to see pride and prejudice. that movie just gets better every time i see it! i love it so much.

this morning i woke up, went to get laura, came home and made pancakes with her... actually i mainly just ate them :D, did some laundry, cleaned some room, put off some homework. you know.. the usual. 


i need a job. asap.

so i'm sitting in the library because i already ate my lunch during english class.. yeah i was pretty hungry. and i can't help but feel slightly nostalgic. i used to come up here during lunch so many times last year so that i could update my LJ and read my friend's posts. 

last year was weird..

life is so weird lately. at times i'm so overjoyed and love every aspect of it and at others i just feel blah. i never really feel THAT upset.. just kinda icky i guess.

school has continued to be great. i honestly don't even mind going anymore because i love seeing all of my friends and even my teachers. senior year is wonderful so far. 

my family has been great as well. me and my mom saw pride and prejudice tonight, which was completely awesome. next on the list of movies to see is rent and tristan and isolde. my sister is back home which is probably the best thing that i could have imagined. sure.. i'm having to get used to cold showers and lots more laundry again, but it's completely worth it. this is what she needs.

in march laura, katie k, katie p, and i are all going to chicago (tentatively) which will be SO much fun. i hope it works out.

boys of course suck as usual and i am bitter towards the species as a whole, but hey what's new?

but basically.. everything else is great.

hope everyone has had a nice start to 2006.

what a fun list that is. i have to pee and am freezing so i'm gonna run. hope everyone has a really great week, does well on their exams (if applicable), and has a very VERY merry christmas.

so.. i haven't updated this baby in like a gazillion years.
everything is going pretty awesome right now.

i have all a's in school (this includes ap calculus and my spalding classes. HECK YES MOTHA FUCKAAAA)
i've been training for the mini, although i've been slacking lately since my partner hurt her knees.
i just got hired at pacsun (i think. it's sort've confusing) and i have orientation saturday.
saturday i also have a 5k with my girls from Brandeis Elementary, where i did my senior service. it was this program called Girls on the Run, me and my friend katie basically helped them train for a 5k and learn healthy life patterns and what not. it was really fun and i'll miss them so much.
i've been hanging out with these girls from Spalding classes- amy and mimi- and they're basically AMAZING! i love em. 
me and my little brother are getting along a lot better lately which i'm so thankful for. he's growing up so much and it kills me!! it seems like he should still think girls are gross and talk like a little bug or something.
me and my friend bobby (who are always off and on) are currently on (meaning we are talking and on the verge of dating) and have been since like august. he makes me REALLY happy and i love it! haha
tomorrow is cousins night and i couldn't be more excited PLUS harry potter and the goblet of fire.     
O H   M Y   G O D .    
let us take a moment of silence for the awesomely wonderful series and now movies. 
oh snap i can't wait!!!

well.. i guess that's about it. i hope everybody else has been doing equally as great.

well, i'm gonna go.

last night was    w e i r d.

for the first 2 hours of my drunkenness i was having a pretty good time, acting stupid, seeing a lot of my friends. then katie got upset about her and zach which made me sad, then i sat with bobby and his bitch nasty friends which made me angry, then katie told me something about this guy mason that made me realize i'm just not going to find a GOOD guy that is actually NICE and HONEST! so basically i was really really drunk and kept having to put up with shittiness and putting these two things together equals me sitting in the bathroom crying. i ended up calling my dad who was at the game and sobbing to him that i wanted to go home with him instead of going out, and i met up with him and we left. he aksed if i was on drugs which made me laugh and i said- no i'm drunk, daddy. then i realized what i said and started crying more because i though i would upset him and i didn't want to get in trouble. then he told me he knew that already and wasn't mad, but glad that i called him.

i really don't understand why i have these little breakdowns randomly. i really don't like the way i am when i drink and i deserve more than to be a stupid drunk girl. the whole drunk high school party scene is just getting so old. i honestly do not want to do this anymore.

anyways.. this weekend was tons of fun.

saturday i went to the cheesecake factory with katie and we split a piece of banana cheesecake and it was SO DELICIOUS! then we went to this girl autumn's party and me and katie left at like 12 to go pick up my brother and his friends. she was drunk and they all knew. it was really funny. then we went back to the party and drank some. the cops showed up, hoppen a 10 foot tall wooden privacy fence. i ran into random pole in the yard and hurt my knee and katie scraped her leg while climbing the fence. the only reason we didn't kill ourselves is because this guy mason caught us. after that we went to st barnabas and played on the playground to kill time before returning to the party. i tried to give katie a piggy back ride and almost killed us. when we got back to our cars we didn't wanna go back into autumn's house because we didn't really know her so we just crashed in our cars. it was probably the most uncomfortable night i've ever had. 
it was still fun though.
hope everyone else had a fun weekend.
